  "prompt": "How long does it take to open a savings bank account in ICICI bank?",
  "response": "Opening a savings bank account in ICICI Bank typically takes about 30 minutes to an hour if you visit a branch in person. This time can vary depending on factors such as the branch's current customer volume and the completeness of your documentation.\n\nIf you choose to open an account online, the process can be quicker, often taking just a few minutes to fill out the necessary forms, provided you have all required documents in digital format. Once submitted, account verification may take a few hours to a couple of days.\n\nTo ensure a smooth process, make sure you have the following documents ready:\n\n1. Identity proof (Aadhaar card, passport, voter ID, etc.).\n2. Address proof (utility bill, rental agreement, etc.).\n3. Passport-sized photographs.\n4. PAN card (if applicable).\n\nFor the most accurate information, it's advisable to check ICICI Bank's official website or contact their customer service.",
